                            <comment id="12784992" author="rding" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2009 20:41:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The script works if the input has no schema:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
A = load &apos;1.txt&apos;;
B = group A by a0;
C = foreach B { D = order A by *; generate group, D;};
explain C;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12785386" author="rding" created="Thu, 3 Dec 2009 16:37:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The above script has a typo. It should be&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
A = load &apos;1.txt&apos;;
B = group A by $0;
C = foreach B { D = order A by *; generate group, D;};
explain C;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12786067" author="rding" created="Fri, 4 Dec 2009 18:48:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The cause of this bug is that the schema of the project &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/star_yellow.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; operator isn&apos;t set correctly before applying ProjectStarTranslator and therefore project &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/star_yellow.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; operator isn&apos;t  translated to a list of projection operators. This causes the inconsistency (and the exception). This patch provides a fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
